What will be repeated vs reused

Because the script did not finish, it likely has to redo model training from the beginning. But this restart should be much faster than a cold run because the heavy embedding caches now exist.

Likely reused:

NAICS semantic memory cache
NAICS feature embeddings
NAICS scoring embeddings
qe4ar semantic memory cache
qe4ar feature embeddings
qe5ar semantic memory cache

Likely still needs to do again:

NAICS supervised model selection/training
qe4ar supervised model selection/training
qe5ar feature embeddings
qe5ar supervised model selection/training
final scoring
saving model and .sav

The biggest loss is that qe4ar supervised training needs to rerun because the bundle was not saved yet. The biggest win is that the very expensive qe4ar and qe5ar embedding work should mostly not rerun.

Step 6: Watch the restart for cache hits

The restart should quickly show lines like:

Loading cached embeddings: ...

For qe5ar, the important one is:

[qe5ar_SOC_semantic_memory] Loading cached embeddings: C:\laborshed_autocode\embedding_cache\qe5ar_SOC_semantic_memory_181fb3dd24a29827fe630aea.npy

Then it should get back to:

[qe5ar] Building features...

without Hugging Face network retries.

Step 7: If it still tries the internet

If you still see lines like:

requesting HEAD https://huggingface.co/...

then offline mode did not reach the Python process. Check the active process command and environment is harder from outside, so the simplest fix is to run the offline load test again in the exact same terminal, then immediately run the autocoder command from that same terminal.

You can also set persistent user-level environment variables:

setx HF_HUB_OFFLINE "1"
setx TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE "1"
setx HF_HUB_DISABLE_PROGRESS_BARS "1"

Then close and reopen Positron/PowerShell.

Only do this after the model is cached. Offline mode will fail if a required model file is not already cached.

